cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper deals with speech-based assessment for identifying Alzheimer's disease, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques for classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of oversampling techniques, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with data sets and their combination, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
